The accuracy of the FFT is measured by the BACC Index, which is calculated based on the amount of correct decisions (Table 1) obtained from the ifan decision algorithm, which is described in detail in previous research79. In summary, the ifan decision algorithm tests several different thresholds of the investigated indices of climate variability to find one that maximizes the predictor’s accuracy. Consequently, once the set of multiple FFTs has been created, ifan selects the decision tree with the highest balanced accuracy.Table 1
